Introduction

DRIPPIN is a six-member South Korean boy group created by Woollim Entertainment.

Before the group's official debut, six out of the seven members were first revealed to the public through the survival show Produce X 101. The youngest, Alex, was eventually revealed as the seventh member on September 11 of the same year. The group eventually debuted on October 28, 2020, with the mini album "Boyager".

On January 26, 2023, Woollim Entertainment announced Alex's hiatus from group activities due to health issues. Six months later, on July 28, the agency revealed that Alex had left the agency and the group for his personal career.
